subject: pciutils version upgrade v3.1.10 -> v3.2.0
commitMessage:
pciutils version upgrade v3.1.10 -> v3.2.0

 -On newer Linux systems, we use libkmod to look up kernel modules
  (modules.pcimap no longer exists.) To facilitate this,
  libpci is able to look up module aliases in sysfs.
 -Various minor bug fixes.
 -Updated pci.ids to the today's snapshot of the database.

Change-Id: Id9b683fdda94715614f073cde0f144155e20bdb5
Signed-off-by: Jae-young Hwang <j-zero.hwang@samsung.com>

comments.message:
Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

This change does not adhere to the Tizen 3.0 submission guidelines for upstream packages.  The (incomplete) documentation for this process is here:

https://source.tizen.org/documentation/reference/git-build-system/upstream-package

The 'upstream' branch needs to be updated first, and optionally, the 'pristine-tar' branch.  Those changes are pushed directly to the git repo, not for review.

Then, the 'tizen' branch should be rebased on top of 'upstream', and then pushed directly to the git repo.

Finally, any further required changes should be pushed for review (refs/for/tizen). Such changes usually include spec file modifications (version update, etc.) and a new changelog entry.
Change has been successfully pushed.

Patch Set 1: Reverted

This patchset was reverted in change: I5ef1114342fa6e866b32a9e24661610dee515d07

subject: Imported Upstream version 3.2.0
commitMessage:
Imported Upstream version 3.2.0

-On newer Linux systems, we use libkmod to look up kernel modules
  (modules.pcimap no longer exists.) To facilitate this,
  libpci is able to look up module aliases in sysfs.
-Various minor bug fixes.
-Updated pci.ids to the today's snapshot of the database.

Change-Id: Ib2c14d285ce84eaeaf2dfacabac12d2e681f7937
Signed-off-by: Jae-young Hwang <j-zero.hwang@samsung.com>
